title: IDCard
position: 91,-1164
---
The <b>ID Card</b> is very important. You must ask every entrant to show you theirs.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

The information in the card is crucial and you need to check it against your documents.
    -> (Continue)
        <<if $seenID is false>>
                {give_id()}
                <<set $seenID = true>>
        <<endif>>
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

<<if $seenTutorial is false>>
    Here, have my card. Drag it onto your table.
        -> (Continue)
        -> (Skip)
            <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
            <<jump EndTutorial>>
<<else>>
    You can check my card. 
        -> (Continue)
        -> (Skip)
            <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
            <<jump EndTutorial>>
<<endif>>

In it you can find personal details like <b>name</b>, <b>photo</b>, <b>eye color</b>, <b>distinctive signs</b>, and so on.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

You must check if the person in front of you matches this information.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

Then there's military info, like <b>ID no.</b>, <b>rank</b>, <b>branch</b> and <b>regiment code</b>.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

<<if $seenTutorial is false>>
    I'll tell you more about these in a moment. Just make sure to check them on the card. Understood?
        -> Yes, Colonel.
            <<jump Badges>>
<<else>>
     You also need to validate those. Understood?
        -> Yes, Colonel.
            <<set $page = 0>>
            <<if $jumpedTutorial>>
                <<jump AskTutorialSkip>>
            <<else>>
                <<jump AskTutorial>>
            <<endif>>
<<endif>>
===

