title: Map
position: 642,-1158
---
Back to the <b>regiment code</b> in the ID Card, each character represents a piece of information.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

The first letter, <b>R</b>, just stands for Regiment.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

The second letter is the <b>branch</b> initial. For example, <b>A</b> stands for Artillery.
    -> (Continue)
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

Finally, there's a number identifying the <b>regiment</b> one is stationed at.
    -> (Continue)
        <<if $gaveMap is false>>
                {give_map()}
                <<set $gaveMap = true>>
        <<endif>>
    -> (Skip)
        <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
        <<jump EndTutorial>>

<<if $seenTutorial is false>>
    This <b>regiment map</b> identifies which cities belong to each regiment.
        -> (Continue)
        -> (Skip)
            <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
            <<jump EndTutorial>>
<<else>>
    The <b>regiment map</b> identifies which cities belong to each regiment.
        -> (Continue)
        -> (Skip)
            <<set $jumpedTutorial = true>>
            <<jump EndTutorial>>
<<endif>>

Ask the attendants where they're stationed and validate it. Understood?
    -> Yes, Colonel.
    <<if $seenTutorial is false>>
        <<jump ParkingSpots>>
    <<else>>
        <<set $page = 0>>
        
        <<if $jumpedTutorial>>
            <<jump AskTutorialSkip>>
        <<else>>
            <<jump AskTutorial>>
        <<endif>>
    <<endif>>
===

